description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decontamination Technician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rare &amp; exciting opportunity has arisen to join our dynamic &amp; busy decontamination team at Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust in the role of Reprocessing Unit Decontamination Technician.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an enthusiastic individual with endoscope decontamination or sterile services experience, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly organised &amp; customer focused team player who will play their part in delivering a smooth &amp; high quality service to multiple clinical areas. The successful candidate will be resilient (able to handle pressured situations &amp; work to tight / changing deadlines), with good communication skills &amp; great attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be primarily responsible for the timely delivery, retrieval &amp; decontamination of flexible endoscopes, along with the accurate completion of associated records. They will adhere to all departmental work instructions &amp; maintain the highest standards of quality control throughout the entire process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very proud of our ISO 13485 certification; all team members are expected to contribute to the evolution of our quality management system, participate in audit &amp; support all ongoing accreditation &amp; quality improvement activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details, informal discussion / visits contact: &lt;br /&gt;Nick Wood - nicholas.wood5@nhs.net / 020 3312 5406.&lt;/p&gt;
